						<summary>

						<p>This fragmentary inscription is dated <hi rend="bold">Bīra-Vikrama year 26, Vishu, • • • • śu 1,</hi> Sunday, probably corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1101, July 18, Sunday,</hi> the month being Adhika-Bhādrapada (not verifiable). It seems to record the death of Kannaseṭṭi in a raid. The district of Tarddavāḍi and the village Niḍuvaṇi are mentioned. Bīra-Vikrama year apparently stands for Chālukya-Vikrama year.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
